The paper focuses on a crowdsourcing platform for robotic skill learning through imitation, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the user interface and user experience of the platform, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of imitation learning for policy learning also falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Lastly, the paper mentions the use of trajectory-based teleoperation, which could relate to computer vision (cs.CV) for tracking and analyzing the trajectories.
